⭐️ Communication Mastery Starts Here! 🙌 Storytelling is the key to being a captivating speaker, check out these tips when it comes to improving your speaking.

Here are 6 tips to help you master communication: 

1. Your Words: Choose your words carefully and make sure they reflect the message you intend to convey. 🤔 #CommunicationMasters 

2. Your Vocabulary: Expand your vocabulary to have a more diverse range of words to express yourself. 🤓 #VocabularyExpansion 

3. Enunciation: Speak clearly so that your message is understood. 🗣 #EnunciationMasters

4. Your Eyes: Maintain eye contact with the person you’re talking to. 🤝 #EyeContactMasters 

5. Your Hands: Use hand gestures to emphasize your point. 👋 #GestureMasters 

6. Speaking Position: Stand up straight and project your voice to your audience. 🔊 #SpeakerPositionMasters 💪

These 5️⃣ practice spots are the perfect way to get started on your public speaking journey. 🎤

First, get friendly feedback from your friends. They can offer valuable insight and support while you practice. Next, hone your skills in the classroom, where you can receive guidance from a teacher or mentor. 👨‍👩‍👧‍👦👨‍🏫📚

Speaking online is also a great way to build your confidence. Try recording yourself and posting your videos on social media for constructive feedback. You can also perfect your delivery by speaking in front of a mirror and watching yourself. 📸

Finally, don't be afraid to speak up at work. This is a great opportunity to showcase your communication skills and build your confidence in a professional setting. 👷‍♂️🗄️

With these 5️⃣ practice spots, you'll be on your way to becoming a pro in no time. Remember, practice makes perfect! 📊📈

Gratitude, Goals, and Living Life Fully 💫🎯

Chris Singleton, the remarkable guest on the Sugar Daddy Podcast, shared his inspiring journey towards achieving his five cherished goals. It’s a testament to the power of clarity and perspective. Let’s dive into Chris’s goals and what they mean to him:

1️⃣ Making a Million: 💰✅
Over the past 12 months, Chris accomplished his first goal - making a million dollars in a year. He acknowledges its significance, but also recognizes that true fulfillment extends beyond the number in his bank account.

2️⃣ Love and Family: ❤️
Chris’s second goal is to ensure his wife’s and children’s love. He understands that success should never come at the expense of the precious bonds he cherishes most.

3️⃣ Unwavering Faith: 🙏
Remaining rooted in his faith is a cornerstone of Chris’s identity. He’s committed to nurturing his spirituality and staying true to his beliefs as he navigates his path.

4️⃣ Generosity and Giving: 🤝
Chris aspires to be a giver, shunning stinginess and embracing a mindset of abundance. By openly sharing his success, he promotes a culture of giving and inspires others to follow suit.

5️⃣ Fitness and Vitality: 💪🌟
Being physically fit is crucial to Chris’s lifestyle. He aims to maintain a healthy and active life, enabling him to fully engage with his children, embracing playful moments and creating lasting memories.

Reflecting on his journey, Chris realized that the pursuit of a million dollars shouldn’t overshadow the importance of quality of life. Beyond a certain point, the incremental financial gains become less impactful compared to the joy of spending meaningful time with loved ones and engaging in fulfilling activities.

Chris’s wisdom reminds us to value the intangible riches that money can’t buy. Let’s cherish our relationships, nurture our faith, give generously, prioritize our well-being, and seize every opportunity to live life to the fullest. #CantLetMomsDown #financialliteracy #financialpodcast #financialfreedom #moneytalk #blackpodcasterscommunity #husbandandwife #wealthbuilding

Honoring my beautiful mother-in-law always! 
-
-
-
-

On June 18th, 2015 I made a promise to Chris. Not knowing what was to come or what to expect I promised him I would always tell our kids about you. 
-
It’s been eight years since I made that promise and it’s been almost six years of me keeping it. As CJ is getting older the questions are getting a little tougher to answer, but we try as hard as we can while trying to keep him innocent for a little longer.
-
But one day CJ , Caden, and baby girl C will understand why daddy works so hard. They’ll understand why we don’t take what Chris said lightly, that “if we just love the way my mom did, the hate won’t be close to where love is.” That despite never getting to be hugged or kissed by you they will know your love. 
-
As always, thank you for the giving me the gift of your son. He is an amazing father and husband. Most importantly he is a God fearing man with a heart of gold. 
-
With love and continuous admiration,
Your daughter in law
-
 I want to thank my sister in law @camrynimani for encouraging me to recreate this photo and @vinnyalmeidaphotography for helping us bring to to fruition.
- 
And yes, CJ is his fathers twin. And Caden gets his spunk from his aunty Cam (aka AC 😂)
